text:
Chrissy Teigen and John Legend are going to need a bigger garage.

Kris Jenner—who is often referred to as the gifting queen by her family and friends—struck again this weekend when she gave the couple's daughter Luna two amazing presents to celebrate her first birthday. The model turned cookbook author shared a photo of the gifts on Twitter over the weekend, and the famous tot received not one, but two mini cars from the Keeping Up with the Kardashians star and matriarch. Luna rwas given a hot pink Barbie Cadillac SUV as well as a Minnie-Mouse themed ride—both wrapped in pretty pink bows.

"I need a bigger garage," Teigen wrote alongside a snap of the extravagant toys. "GIFTING QUEEN DOES IT AGAIN @krisjenner you are BONKERS we love you." Can we get some love on our birthday, Kris?

I need a bigger garage. GIFTING QUEEN DOES IT AGAIN @krisjenner you are BONKERS we love youpic.twitter.com/TltEu4l4z8 — christine teigen (@chrissyteigen) April 15, 2017

Teigen and Legend also got their little one some pretty cool presents for her special day, including a pink toy kitchen that came complete with fake food and utensils, a pink and purple Little Tikes shopping cart and car combo, and a beautifully decorated cake handmade by her parents.

RELATED: How Chrissy Teigen and John Legend's Daughter Luna Celebrated Her 1st Birthday

Definitely not a bad way to celebrate turning one.
